      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Absolutely not; you must never give aspirin to a child under 16 due to the risk of Reye's syndrome, a rare but fatal condition that causes liver and brain damage. Instead, you should immediately administer a dose of acetaminophen (Tylenol) or ibuprofen (Motrin) at the correct pediatric dosage for an 8-year-old, which is typically 10-15 mg/kg every 4-6 hours. If the fever persists, the child becomes lethargic, or you see other concerning symptoms, you should contact your pediatrician right away for further guidance.",
